==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pœcilitic
<hw>P⟦oe⟧`ci*lit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>poiki`los</grk> many-colored, variegated.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Mottled with various colors; variegated; spotted; --
said of certain rocks.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Specifically: Of or
pertaining to, or characterizing, Triassic and Permian sandstones of red
and other colors.</def> <altsp>[Also written
<asp>poikilitic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poecilopod</ent>⟦br⟧
